ose specific dollar amounts or average selling prices for the kits. It only states that the standalone selling price is determined based on the price at which the kit is sold separately to similar customers in similar locations.\n*   **Margins:** No explicit gross margin percentages or dollar amounts for kit margins are disclosed. However, the filings note that "Starlink Kit costs" are a component of the Connectivity segment\'s cost of revenue. The company expects these costs to decrease as a percentage of revenue over time as it drives efficiencies in next-generation Starlink Kits. Additionally, the text mentions that a $39 million decrease in impairment charges in 2025 was related to the discontinuation of a Starlink Kit production line.\n*   **Volumes:** Specific unit volumes (e.g., number of kits sold) are not disclosed. However, the MD&A references "higher kit deliveries" driving a $907 million increase in volume spend on Starlink Kits in 2024. It also notes R&D expense increases in 2025 ($22 million) and Q1 2026 ($8 million) specifically tied to the next-generation production development of Starlink Kits.',
