ion shifts again. The "mobile connectivity business" is broken out as a standalone sub-component parallel to—rather than nested within—a newly labeled "aviation, maritime, and other enterprise business" category. This period also marks the only time one of the sub-components (government connectivity) is reported as a decrease rather than growth.',
