aphic mix shifts quantitatively, cannot assess subscriber retention/lifetime economics, and cannot allocate deferred revenue or backlog to Connectivity. These gaps are particularly material for the E&G line, which grew from $1,052M (FY2023) to $4,179M (FY2025)—a 4× increase driven by streams whose individual scales and trajectories are not disclosed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n{\\n  \\"sources\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\"url\\": \\"https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm\\",\\n      \\"name\\": \\"SpaceX S-1 Registration Statement (filed May 20, 2026) — Connectivity segment disclosures, revenue disaggregation tables, MD&A growth narratives, ARPU/subscriber definitions, and segment financial metrics\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}"}',
